edu.ucsd.ccdb.ontomorph2.core.tangible
Class Tangible

java.lang.Object
  java.util.Observable
      edu.ucsd.ccdb.ontomorph2.core.tangible.Tangible
All Implemented Interfaces:
ISemanticsAware, ISelectable
Direct Known Subclasses:
Axon, ContainerTangible, Curve3D, CurveAnchorPoint, NeuroMLNetwork, NeuronMorphology, Slide, SphereParticles, Surface
public abstract class Tangible
extends java.util.Observable
implements ISemanticsAware

Defines an object that can be viewed in the scene. This object can be made relative to an arbitrary coordinate system.

Author:
Stephen D. Larson (slarson@ncmir.ucsd.edu)
See Also:
ICoordinateSystem

getWorldNormal

public OMTVector getWorldNormal()
Returns a vector representing the normal of the XY plane of the parent tangible Takes the cross of the X and Y and then rotates it about the CoordinateSystem of the source Tangible The vector returned is in Absoltue World Coordinates

Returns:
OMTVector represrnting the normal in JME world coordinates

rotate

public void rotate(float dx,
                   float dy,
                   OMTVector constraint)
Changes the rotation of this Tangible

Parameters:
morph - the item(s) to be rotated
constraint - the axis (or axes) on which to rotate the object. For example, if constraint is (1,0,0) the object will rotates about it's own X axis (not the world's X axis)
